results.name: Number of not necessarily connected 8-regular simple graphs on n vertices.
comment: The Euler transformation currently does nothing: for n < 18, a(n) = A014378(n).
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Octic Graph
mathematica: EulerTransform[Rest @ A014378] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Dec 04 2019, updated Mar 18 2020 *)
xref: 8-regular simple graphs: A014378 (connected), A165878 (disconnected), this sequence (not necessarily connected).

Not necessarily connected regular simple graphs: A005176 (any degree), A051031 (triangular array), specified degree k: A000012 (k=0), A000012 (k=1), A008483 (k=2), A005638 (k=3), A033301 (k=4), A165626 (k=5), A165627 (k=6), A165628 (k=7), this sequence (k=8).
8-regular not necessarily connected graphs: this sequence (simple graphs), A129437 (multigraphs with loops allowed), A129426 (multigraphs with loops forbidden).
